{"published time": "2024-03-30T15:21:00+08:00", "images": ["https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/3-17.jpg", "https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2-12.jpg", "https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/1-15.jpg"], "content": "<div class=\"single-content\"><figure class=\"post-thumbnail\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"395\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-30T15-21-00-08-00/000000.jpg\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-30T15-21-00-08-00/000000.jpg\" width=\"593\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Members of the Canadian Armed Forces train members of the Armed Forces of Ukraine to detect landmines, as part of Operation UNIFIER, in the United Kingdom on February 1, 2024.\n\nImage by Master Corporal Justin Roy, Canadian Armed Forces\n20240201AKAO0011D002</figcaption></figure><!-- .post-thumbnail --><p><strong>Canada's Armed Forces are teaching the soldiers of the Armed Forces of Ukraine how to identify, avoid and dispose of explosive objects.</strong></p><p>About this<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/GeneralStaff.ua/posts/pfbid0QgyagaPKJtEKUfocwuDiA5s1yvvztvRTbHSDGhk5f5Vo5P53qLS6arQm3zCcgZjdl\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">reported</a>The General Staff of the Armed Forces of Ukraine.</p><p>Canadian military stationed in the United Kingdom as part of the Multinational Interflex Educational Operation and that is where they conduct training for our soldiers.</p><div class=\"fotorama--wp\" data-auto=\"false\" data-captiontag=\"dd\" data-columns=\"0\" data-icontag=\"dt\" data-ids=\"560691,560690\" data-itemtag=\"dl\" data-link=\"file\" data-max-width=\"100%\" data-ratio=\"1.5025041736227\" data-size=\"large\" data-width=\"1800\"><div class=\"gallery galleryid-560688 gallery-columns-0 gallery-size-thumbnail\" id=\"gallery-1\"><dl class=\"gallery-item\"><dt class=\"gallery-icon landscape\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-30T15-21-00-08-00/000001.jpg\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-30T15-21-00-08-00/000001.jpg\" width=\"150\"/></dt></dl><dl class=\"gallery-item\"><dt class=\"gallery-icon portrait\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-30T15-21-00-08-00/000002.jpg\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-30T15-21-00-08-00/000002.jpg\" width=\"150\"/></dt></dl></div></div><p>Mines and other explosive objects pose a constant danger on the modern battlefield.</p><p>\"The Armed Forces are grateful for the support and assistance of Canada and the United Kingdom,\" the General Staff said.</p><p>Earlier, the Armed Forces General Staff showed how Ukrainian servicemen under the guidance of Australian instructors of the Kudu operation operation<a href=\"https://armyinform.com.ua/2024/03/19/na-brytanskomu-poligoni-voyiny-zsu-vidpraczyuvaly-elementy-boyu-v-umovah-miskoyi-zabudovy/\">worked out</a>Skills of the area with suburban construction, including storming and cleaning of buildings.</p></div>", "source": "https://armyinform.com.ua/2024/03/30/kanadski-instruktory-u-brytaniyi-navchayut-voyiniv-zsu-zneshkodzhuvaty-vybuhonebezpechni-predmety/", "title": "Canadian instructors in Britain teach the Armed Forces warriors to neutralize explosive objects", "description": "This was reported by the General Staff of the Armed Forces of Ukraine. Canadian military stationed in ...", "author": ["Army Inform"], "categories": ["\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438"], "tags": ["\u0412\u0435\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0411\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0456\u044f", "\u0406\u041d\u0422\u0415\u0420\u0424\u041b\u0415\u041a\u0421", "\u041a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0434\u0430"], "source_name": "ArmyInform"}